# ATLASSIAN LINK FORMAT [MUST]

## Rule LINK.0: User-facing URLs

Confluence wiki and Jira may live on **different** hosts. Values come from `.env` (`CONFLUENCE_WIKI_BASE`, `JIRA_BASE_URL`) set by `setup.ps1`.

| System | Pattern |
|--------|---------|
| **Confluence** | `{CONFLUENCE_WIKI_BASE}/spaces/{CONFLUENCE_SPACE}/pages/{pageId}/{Title+slug}` |
| **Jira** | `{JIRA_BASE_URL}/browse/{ISSUE_KEY}` |

**Forbidden in deliverables:** REST API URLs as primary user links.

---

## Rule LINK.1: Confluence page links

```markdown
[Page title]({CONFLUENCE_WIKI_BASE}/spaces/{CONFLUENCE_SPACE}/pages/{pageId}/{Title+With+Plus+Encoding})
```

Encode title: spaces to `+`, `/` to `%2F`.

---

## Rule LINK.2: Jira ticket links

```markdown
[{TICKET_PREFIX}-123]({JIRA_BASE_URL}/browse/{TICKET_PREFIX}-123)
```

---

## Rule LINK.3: Where this applies

Chat reports, test cases, bug validation, and expert Q&A deliverables that cite wiki or Jira.

---

## Rule LINK.4: MCP / REST vs user links

MCP/REST use API bases internally. User-facing citations use LINK.1 / LINK.2 patterns with hosts from `.env`.
